article.description: — Ryan Allen scored 23 points as Delaware narrowly beat Drexel 81-77 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Allen leads Delaware past Drexel 81-77
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Ryan Allen scored 23 points as Delaware narrowly beat Drexel 81-77 on Tuesday night. Jameer Nelson Jr. added 20 points for for Delaware (11-5, 2-1 Colonial Athletic Association). Dylan Painter had 14 points and nine rebounds Andrew Carr added 10 points. Xavier Bell had 18 points for the Dragons (6-6, 1-1). Melik Martin added 16 points and seven rebounds. Amari Williams had 15 points, seven rebounds and three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
